DUBAI: US actress Lindsay Lohan is still celebrating her love. For the latest updates, follow us on Instagram @arabnews.lifestyle The “Mean Girls” star, who lives in Dubai, celebrated her engagement to financier Bader Shammas in Kuwait on Tuesday. The actress shared a picture of her and Shammas on Instagram standing behind a white and blue two-tier cake that had an engagement ring on it and read: “He asked, she said yes.” “My forever,” wrote Lohan, captioning the image. A post shared by Lindsay Lohan (@lindsaylohan) The Hollywood star announced her engagement in November, posting a series of snaps that showed off her diamond engagement ring. The actress and financier were first spotted together at a music festival in Dubai shortly before the pandemic hit in 2020. In May 2020, the “Mean Girls” star’s mother Dina Lohan spoke of Shammas, saying: “Lindsay is dating a wonderful guy right now, but that’s neither here nor there. When she’s ready to talk about her personal life, she will.”